Install AMP(APACHE,MySQL,php) software stack.

1) WAMP for Windows
2) LAMP for Linux
3) MAMP for Mac
4) SAMP for Solaris
5) FAMP for FreeBSD
6) XAMPP (Cross, Apache, MySQL, PHP, Perl) for Cross Platform: 
           It includes some other components too such as FileZilla, OpenSSL, Webalizer, Mercury Mail, etc.


RUN PHP CODE IN XAMPP
***************************************
1) Save file as .php
   ex: Hello.php ---> file name
       <!DOCTYPE>  
       <html>  
       <body>  
       <?php  
       echo "<h2>Hello First PHP</h2>";  
       ?>  
       </body>  
       </html>  
    Output:

       Hello First PHP

2) There is a "htdocs" directory in XAMPP (CHECK which folder u installed xampp.).
3) Save php file to htdocs.
4) Open XAMPP ----> START Apache and MySQL
5) Open web browser and type ----->
      localhost http://localhost/Hello.php 